text: Sylvirana faber is a frog. It lives in the hills in Cambodia and Thailand. The adult frog is 59.4 mm long from nose to rear end. The head is long and narrow. There are eight vomerine teeth in its jaw. This frog is light brown in color on the back and dark brown on the sides and eardrum. There are stripes of dark brown on its legs. The belly is white and the insides of the legs are pink. There are disks for climbing on its toes. Scientists say this frog is related to Rana nigrovittata and Rana mortenseni. ==References== Category:Frogs of Asia Category:IUCN Red List vulnerable species
title: Sylvirana faber
